Oil producers , consumers to meet in S . Africa in 97 . The next meeting of world oil producing and consuming nations will be held in South Africa in 1997 , a member of this year ' s host delegation India said on Sunday . The meeting will be the sixth between oil importing and exporting nations since the dialogues began in the wake of the Gulf War oil price scare . Further details on the conference were not available . Producers and consumers were wrapping up the last day of talks in this tourist resort state on Sunday . Discussions so far have centred on security of energy supplies , the importance of stable prices , investment requirements and ways to meet the growing energy needs of emerging economies . Delegates have also floated the idea of using the forums to develop a global energy organisation to collect data and possibly ideas for more unified world energy policies . 
